      "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
      "body": "I agree and think that this can be closed, [this line](https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/blob/f4a8269dfc144cc918570bdb870aa5143a11c1fe/src/net_processing.cpp#LL5513C20-L5513C32) sends out the \"initial getheaders\" to one or more peers only after the reindex is finished (`m_blockman.LoadingBlocks()` switches to false, and `fSyncStarted` cannot be true before that). This should be independent of whether any new blocks were found during the reindex or not.",
